Centralized Systems:
- Every thing goes to one node of object(all stores in one place)
- Most systems we are use today are centralized
- Systems controlled by a single entity
- Examples: Google, Governments, Local and Central Banks, iMessage, WhatsApp, Messanger, Amazon, Most Exchanges
 -- even coinBase is also the centralized.

 Decentralization: It is the process by which the activities of an orgonization, particularly those regarding planning and decision making, are distributed or delegated away from a central, authoritative location or group.
- multiples nodes are connected to each othes.
- Decentralized systems aloow for trust-less interactions


